H2      2.6.    Tagging
div(id="26")
  h3    Tagging
  p      Typically people use this functionality to mark release points (v1.0, and so on).
  h3    Listing Your Tags
  p      [$ git tag]
  p    You can also search for tags with a particualar pattern like this
  p    [$ git tag -l 'v1.*']
  h3    Creating Tags
  p    Git uses two main types of tags:
    li      lightweight
    li      annotated.
  p    A lightweight tag is very much like a branch that doesn’t change – it’s just a pointer to a specific commit.
  p    Annotated tags, are stored as full objects in the Git database
  p    (including the tagger name, e-mail, date;
  p    a tagging message; and can be signed / verified with GNU Privacy Guard (GPG).)
  h3    Annotated Tags
  p    The easiest way is to specify [-a | -m | -s ]: [$ git -a ]
