  p    Like reset, checkout manipulates the three trees, and it is a bit different
  p    depending on whether you give the command a file path or not.
  h3    Without Paths
  p    [$ git checkout [branch] is pretty similar to running [$ git reset --hard [branch]]
  p    in that it updates all three trees for you to look like [branch]
  p    but there are two important differences:
  p
    ol
      li Checkout will check to make sure it’s not blowing away files that have changes to them.
      li Checkout will move HEAD itself to point to another branch (ulike reset that will move the branch that HEAD points to)

  h3    With Paths
  p    [$ git checkout [REF] file]
  p    In that case checkout updates the index with that file at that commit,
  p    but it also overwrites the file in the working directory.
